g.text: The Google Maps API allow for the embedding of Google Maps onto
web pages of outside developers, using a simple JavaScript interface
or a Flash interface. It is designed to work on both mobile devices as
well as traditional desktop browser applications. The API includes
language localization for over 50 languages, region localization and
geocoding, and has mechanisms for enterprise developers who want
to utilize the Google Maps API within an intranet. The API HTTP services
can be accessed over a secure (HTTPS) connection by Google Maps
